text: Paralida triannulata is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Clarke in 1958. It is found in Japan and Taiwan.Paralida at funet The wingspan is 22–24 mm. The forewings are buff shaded with olivaceous.Ent. News 69 (1) : 2 The larvae feed on Melia azedarach var. japonica. ==References== Category:Chelariini Category:Moths described in 1958
title: Paralida triannulata
